  titleZH: "基于 AI 智能体的 Web 知识采集管理系统设计与实现",
  abstractZH: [
    随着互联网信息规模持续增长，个人学习、科研阅读和日常资料整理过程中产生了大量网页、PDF 文档和片段化文本。传统收藏夹、截图和手工笔记方式虽然能够保存信息，但缺乏统一的语义组织、可追溯引用和面向自然语言问题的知识复用能力，导致后续检索和整理成本较高。针对上述问题，本文围绕 Web 场景下的个人知识采集与管理需求，设计并实现了一套基于 AI 智能体的知识采集管理系统 Hachi。

    本文主要工作包括以下三个方面。首先，针对多来源非结构化内容难以统一入库的问题，设计并实现了文本、URL、PDF 上传以及 Chrome 浏览器插件采集等多种知识导入方式，插件进一步支持网页划线、整页正文和框选截图采集，并通过视觉模型将截图内容转换为可检索文本。其次，针对生成式问答容易脱离事实依据的问题，构建了基于检索增强生成的智能问答流程，采用 LangGraph 组织路由智能体、工具调用、证据包构建和答案生成过程，使系统能够结合本地知识库、会话记忆和可选联网搜索生成带引用的回答。最后，针对长期对话中用户偏好、薄弱知识点、邮件事项和回答结果复用难以沉淀的问题，设计了会话记忆压缩、个性化回答调优、Skill 辅助处理和本地提醒机制，将稳定回答偏好和弱点主题写入个人画像工作区，并提供笔记摘要、检测题、复习卡片、行动清单、邮件定时提醒和自定义处理等扩展能力。

    系统采用 FastAPI 作为后端服务框架，使用 SQLite 保存文档、片段、会话和提醒数据，使用 Milvus 或内存向量库完成语义检索，前端以三栏式知识工作台展示来源、对话、引用、工具轨迹、Skill 结果和待触发提醒，浏览器侧基于 Chrome Manifest V3 实现划线采集、整页采集和框选截图采集。测试结果表明，系统已经完成知识入库、语义检索、RAG 问答、会话记忆、截图分析入库、Skill 调用、邮件提醒创建和插件上报等核心流程，能够支撑 Web 知识采集管理场景下的完整使用链路。
  ],
  keywordsZH: ("AI 智能体", "知识管理", "检索增强生成", "多模态采集", "浏览器插件"),

  titleEN: "Design and Implementation of a Web Knowledge Acquisition and Management System Based on AI Agents",
  abstractEN: [
    With the continuous growth of Web information, personal learning, research reading, and daily knowledge organization involve a large amount of web pages, PDF documents, and fragmented text. Traditional bookmarks, screenshots, and manual notes can preserve information, but they usually lack unified semantic organization, traceable citations, and natural language based knowledge reuse. As a result, users still face high costs when retrieving, understanding, and reusing previously collected information. To address these problems, this thesis designs and implements Hachi, a Web knowledge acquisition and management system based on AI agents.

    The main work of this thesis consists of three parts. First, to unify heterogeneous unstructured content, the system supports text input, URL ingestion, PDF upload, and Chrome extension based web clipping. The extension supports selected text, readable page content, and user-selected screenshot regions. Screenshot content is analyzed by a vision-capable model and converted into searchable textual knowledge. Second, to reduce unsupported generation in question answering, the system builds a retrieval-augmented generation workflow. LangGraph is used to orchestrate routing decisions, tool calls, evidence packing, and answer generation, enabling the system to generate cited answers from local knowledge, session memory, and optional web search. Third, to preserve user preferences, weak knowledge topics, email-related tasks, and reusable answer results in long-term interactions, the system implements memory compression, personalized answer tuning, skill-based auxiliary processing, and local reminder scheduling. Stable preferences and weak topics are written to a profile workspace, while built-in skills support note summarization, quiz generation, flashcards, action plans, email reminders, and custom transformations.

    The backend is implemented with FastAPI. SQLite stores documents, chunks, chat sessions, and reminder records, while Milvus or an in-memory vector store provides semantic retrieval. The frontend provides a three-column knowledge workspace for source management, dialogue, citations, tool traces, skill results, and pending reminders. The browser extension is implemented with Chrome Manifest V3 and supports selected-text clipping, full-page content extraction, and screenshot-region capture. The testing results show that the system has completed the core workflow of knowledge ingestion, semantic retrieval, RAG-based question answering, session memory, screenshot analysis, skill execution, email reminder creation, and extension submission, thereby supporting an end-to-end Web knowledge acquisition and management scenario.
  ],
  keywordsEN: ("AI Agent", "Knowledge Management", "Retrieval-Augmented Generation", "Multimodal Capture", "Browser Extension"),
  equation-numbering-location: right + bottom,
